# Git Milestone Rules — Menu Grading Tool

## Auto-Commit Protocol
- Commit after each logical unit of work (a complete component, a full API route, a service module)
- Never commit broken code — run checks first
- Push to GitHub at every milestone

## Commit Message Format
- Prefix with agent label: `[AGENT-N] descriptive message`
- Tag milestones: `[MILESTONE] description`

## Milestone Definitions
1. **Foundation** — Project scaffolding, DB schema (incl Builder, QualitySnapshot), auth, basic routing
2. **Grading Engine** — All rubric logic, scoring functions, automated checks
3. **Upload Pipeline** — PDF/image parsing, OCR, AI extraction, catalog fetching, builder attribution input
4. **Report UI & Feedback** — Score displays, per-item grading, comparison views, feedback email preview/send
5. **Claude AI Layer** — Adaptive learning, pattern recognition, per-builder coaching, insights dashboard
6. **Quality Tracking & Analytics** — Quality snapshots, builder profiles, grader metrics, team dashboards, SLA tracking
7. **Review Workflow & Notifications** — Approval flow, direct-send vs review-then-send, notifications, audit trail, role-based views
8. **Polish & Deploy** — Error handling, auto-save, loading states, responsive design, deployment

## Push Schedule
- Push after completing each milestone
- Push after any critical bug fix
- Push at end of each work session

## Branch Strategy
- `main` — stable, production-ready code
- `feature/*` — feature branches for each milestone
- Merge to main via PR after milestone completion
